OpenAI's Swarm is an experimental framework designed to support multi-agent systems. It focuses on making agent coordination and execution lightweight, controllable, and testable. It utilizes two main abstractions: Agents and handoffs. Agents encompass instructions and tools, and can hand off conversations to other agents. Swarm is still in the experimental stage and may change in the future. For more information, check the GitHub repository: https://github.com/openai/swarm
